{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Declare the third Friday in March \u2018National Climate Day\u2019",
        "additional_details": "In the spirit of the global youth climate strikes of 15 March 2019, we must instigate a culture of engagement in order to recognise the urgency of the situation and ensure we preserve the planet for future generations.\r\n\r\nOur proposed National Climate Day would involve:\r\n\u2022Corporations setting and reviewing their carbon reduction targets\r\n\u2022Schools focusing a day of the year on climate change\r\n\u2022Government raising awareness of climate change and informing the public of our progress in tackling emissions",
        "background": "The latest IPCC report on climate change gives us until 2030 to ensure that global warming does not overshoot a 1.5\u00b0C increase to catastrophic consequences.\r\n\r\nDeclare an annual day of reflection on how we as a nation are tackling carbon targets, and of celebration where we have achieved them.",
